From 436d42df667ad0b24d24ebb103b613defe0bbd03 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kamil Lulko <kamil.lulko@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 22:12:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] =?UTF-8?q?fex-pivot:=20wine=20patch=20013=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20allow=20SetFocus=20on=20top-level=20WS=5FCHILD?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

NtUserSetFocus rejected windows whose only parent is the desktop and
which have WS_CHILD without WS_POPUP. Same pattern as patch 012 for
the wineserver foreground gate: VST plugin editors hit this every
time, and JUCE's grabKeyboardFocus → SetFocus → 0 → JUCE never
commits its internal "currentlyFocusedComponent". Allow the focus
chain to proceed; set_focus_window further down does the actual
work via wineserver (no WS_CHILD restriction there).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
